Name: UCSB
Description: A great university located along the California coast!

Name: Machu Picchu
Description: A Inca city built in the 15th and 16th centuries, now one of the most breathtaking tourist spots in the world.

Name: The Taj Mahal
Description: Built in the 1600's, the Taj Mahal is one of the new Seven Wonders of the World, and is the most famous site in India.

Name: Eiffel Tower
Description: The symbol of Paris, the Eiffel tower was only meant to last 20 years, but has become one of the most famous landmarks in the world.

Name: Santorini, Greece
Description: Filled with white-blue buildings and cliffs, Santorini offers a beautiful view of the sea and romantic tourist destination.

Name: Niagara Falls
Description: An massive and impressive waterfall of over 3100 tons of water, Niagara Falls is a natural wonder and a popular destination among travelers.
